==English==
===Etymology===
[[Latin]] ''intercalare'' to announce an extra day in the calendar.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|intercalate|intercalates|intercalated|intercalating}}
# to insert an extra day or month into a calendar in order to maintain its [[synchrony]] with a natural [[phenomenon]].

